Spiekenisse, a rare sleeping town under Rotterdam, has an unusual record.
Its population of 80,000 has the lowest level of education in the Netherlands.
To combat this embarrassing circumstance a few years ago, it was decided to contribute to general education and build seven fictional bridges, which are depicted on euro banknotes, in the form of painted miniatures made of reinforced concrete.
The success of this educational initiative was modest.
