The project also participates in the 2012 Dutch National Wood Construction Competition.
Thus, the impersonal suburb, which had never been able to offer anything other than the postmodernist pedestrian zone and the surprisingly unbelievably beautiful town hall, whose white facades suggest the idea of a dairy factory, became richer on one modern work of architecture.
